  v1.0.5 Round-6 Rev49 changes:
    - MainActivity.java (AGPL v3): New fields stabilizationHelper +
      stabilizationEnabled. New toggleStabilization() method (sensor
      registration + Toast). New showToastLocalized() (zh/en). onPause/onResume/
      onDestroy lifecycle management for stabilization. VERSION → v1.0.5.
    - StockfishNative.java (GPL v3): New @JavascriptInterface toggleStabilization()
      delegates to MainActivity. ENGINE_VERSION → v1.0.5.
    - StabilizationHelper.java (AGPL v3, NEW FILE): Sensor-fusion anti-shake
      helper. Fuses accelerometer, linear acceleration, gravity, gyroscope,
      rotation vectors. High-pass gravity separation, double integration,
      decay, ±8px clamp, 60Hz JS callback throttle.

  v1.0.5 Round-6 Rev50 changes:
    - MainActivity.java (AGPL v3): No changes (version already v1.0.5 from Rev49).
    - StockfishNative.java (GPL v3): No changes.
    - StabilizationHelper.java (AGPL v3): CRITICAL FIX — anti-shake direction.
      boardPxX/boardPxY now NEGATED (-dispX*SCALE / -dispY*SCALE) so the board
      moves OPPOSITE to device motion (true OIS behavior). Previously +dispX
      amplified shake.
    - ChessApp.java (AGPL v3): Init log version v1.0.4→v1.0.5.
    - ChessWebViewClient.java (AGPL v3): Version comment v1.0.4→v1.0.5.

  v1.0.5 Round-6 Rev51 changes:
    - StabilizationHelper.java (AGPL v3): CRITICAL FIX — anti-shake Y-axis
      direction. Rev50 negated Y (-dispY) which amplified vertical shake.
      Corrected to +dispY (Y NOT negated) per Android sensor Y (up) vs CSS
      screen Y (down) opposite-direction analysis. X remains -dispX (negated).

  v1.0.5 Round-6 Rev52 changes:
    - StabilizationHelper.java (AGPL v3): COMPLETE REWRITE — added screen
      orientation adaptation via WindowManager.getDefaultDisplay().getRotation().
      Per-orientation remap (ROTATION_0/90/180/270) of device displacement to
      screen board displacement. Adjusted decay coefficients. Fixed finalJs
      variable scoping.

  v1.0.5 Round-6 Rev53 changes:
    - StabilizationHelper.java (AGPL v3): REWRITE — only TYPE_LINEAR_ACCELERATION
      + TYPE_ROTATION_VECTOR sensors (removed accelerometer, gyroscope, gravity,
      game/geomagnetic rotation vectors). Added ±2° tilt compensation via
      getRotationMatrixFromVector()+getOrientation(). Display.getRotation()
      for orientation. New applyTransform(x,y,rot) with --stab-rot CSS var.

  v1.0.5 Round-6 Rev54 changes (this round, per user spec items 5-6):
    - StabilizationHelper.java (AGPL v3): TWO improvements per user spec:
      (5) Roll-only rotation — per user spec item 5 ("棋盘旋转应该只考虑屏幕
          向左或右的侧向转动倾斜(roll), 不考虑俯仰倾斜(pitch)或如开关一
          扇门般的旋转(yaw)"). The board's tilt-compensation rotation now
          uses ONLY screen-roll (the steering-wheel tilt of the screen as
          seen by the user). Screen-pitch (nodding) and screen-yaw (door-
          like horizontal turn) are NOT compensated. The implementation
          computes device-frame devPitchDelta and devRollDelta, then
          selects ONLY the one that corresponds to "screen roll" in the
          current display orientation:
            ROTATION_0   (portrait):        screen-roll = -devRollDelta
            ROTATION_90  (landscape-left):  screen-roll = -devPitchDelta
            ROTATION_180 (upside-down):     screen-roll = +devRollDelta
            ROTATION_270 (landscape-right): screen-roll = +devPitchDelta
          (In landscape, the device's pitch axis becomes the screen's roll
          axis due to the 90° rotation — this is correct, NOT a use of
          "pitch" in the user-spec sense.) Renamed local vars from dPitch/
          dRoll to devPitchDelta/devRollDelta + screenRollDeg for clarity.
          Updated the JavaDoc with a detailed explanation of the screen-
          roll concept.
      (6) First-principles anti-shake audit — per user spec item 6 and the
          two uploaded sensor reference docs. Added a 10-point audit section
          at the top of the file cross-checking every sensor choice and
          parameter against the technical report. Key change: PREFER
          TYPE_GAME_ROTATION_VECTOR (no magnetometer → no magnetic drift
          near laptops/metal desks/elevators, per technical report §6.3.1)
          with fallback to TYPE_ROTATION_VECTOR if the game-rotation variant
          is unavailable. The onSensorChanged handler now accepts both
          TYPE_ROTATION_VECTOR and TYPE_GAME_ROTATION_VECTOR (same data
          format). Audit VERIFIED (no change needed): SENSOR_DELAY_GAME
          sampling rate, α=0.15 low-pass filter, 0.3° dead zone, decay-
          based drift prevention (instead of zero-bias calibration),
          lifecycle register/unregister pattern, graceful null-sensor
          fallback. Audit CONFIRMED: TYPE_ORIENTATION / device_orientation
          sensor is deprecated (doc B confirms) — we correctly use
          Display.getRotation() instead.

  v1.0.5 Round-6 Rev55 changes (line-by-line code audit, per user request):
    First-principles audit of every file's every line. Six improvements found,
    prioritized: bug fixes > feature completion > perf > redundancy > simplification.
    - StatsActivity.java (AGPL v3): THREE bug fixes (security + Android-15 compat):
      (a) WebView security parity with MainActivity — added setAllowFileAccess(false),
          setAllowContentAccess(false), setAllowFileAccessFromFileURLs(false),
          setAllowUniversalAccessFromFileURLs(false), setMixedContentMode(NEVER_ALLOW),
          setDisplayZoomControls(false), setUseWideViewPort(true),
          setLoadWithOverviewMode(true), setTextZoom(100). The stats WebView was
          missing these defense-in-depth flags, leaving a weaker attack surface.
      (b) FLAG_FULLSCREEN deprecation fix — was using FLAG_FULLSCREEN unconditionally,
          which conflicts with Edge-to-Edge enforcement on API 35+ (causes black
          screen on HyperOS 3, same bug MainActivity fixed in v18.4.6). Now gated
          on SDK_INT < R, matching MainActivity.
      (c) Immersive mode added — the stats page now hides system bars (status +
          navigation) just like the main game, using the same platform-aware
          approach (WindowInsetsController on API 30+, legacy flags on API 21-29).
          Added _applyImmersiveMode() + _applyLegacyImmersive() + onWindowFocusChanged().
      Also added setBackgroundColor(#1a0a0a) to avoid white flash on load, and
      setFilterTouchesWhenObscured(true) for tapjacking defense (both matching
      MainActivity).
    - StockfishNative.java (GPL v3): BUG FIX in engineGoDepth — was missing
      applyEvalModeOptions() call (sets Contempt=0, MultiPV=1, UCI_ShowWDL=true
      for objective analysis). Without it, deep eval searches ran with gameplay
      Contempt=24 (biased toward avoiding draws) and the user's MultiPV setting
      (potentially >1, reducing search depth). engineEval already had this call;
      engineGoDepth was missing it (oversight when engineGoDepth was added).
    - worker-pool.js (AGPL v3): consistency fix — the worker's fenToState()
      checked `parts.length<4`, while the main-thread fenToState in
      tablebase.js checks `parts.length<2`. Changed worker to `<2` for
      consistency.
    - game-logic.js (GPL v3): PERF optimization in getCtrlMap — hoisted the
      attacker-position object out of the inner loop. Each piece at (r,c)
      attacks multiple squares, but its `position` field is the SAME for all
      those pushes. Previously allocated a fresh {row:r,col:c} object on every
      push (~256 allocations per ctrl-map = per render tick when heatmap is on).
      Now allocates ONE position object per piece (max 32) and reuses it.
    - chess960.js (AGPL v3): cleaned up misleading stale comment in
      parseShredderCastling() — the comment claimed the prior line was "dead
      code" but that was already consolidated in v1.0.4. The code was correct;
      only the comment was stale.
    - EngineService.java (AGPL v3): redundancy cleanup — extracted shared
      notification-builder logic into _buildNotificationWithContent(). Both
      buildNotification() (instance) and updateNotification() (static) now
      delegate to this helper, eliminating ~50 lines of duplicated builder
      configuration.

  v1.0.5 Round-6 Rev58 changes (magnetic-field-aware sensor switching):
    - StabilizationHelper.java (AGPL v3): REWrote the rotation sensor
      selection logic per user spec. New strategy:
      (1) On start, use TYPE_ROTATION_VECTOR (magnetometer+accel+gyro
          fusion) — ensures accurate baseline orientation.
      (2) Register TYPE_MAGNETIC_FIELD (android.sensor.magnetic_field) in
          the background at SENSOR_DELAY_UI (~16 Hz).
      (3) Compute magnetic field magnitude |B| = sqrt(x²+y²+z²) on each
          event. Maintain a rolling baseline via slow low-pass filter
          (α=0.05 — adapts over ~20 samples, ignores transient spikes).
      (4) When |current - baseline| > 15 µT (MAGNETIC_DISTURBANCE_THRESHOLD),
          switch to TYPE_GAME_ROTATION_VECTOR (no magnetometer — immune to
          magnetic interference). Reset tilt baseline to avoid a jump.
      (5) When |current - baseline| < 8 µT (MAGNETIC_CALM_THRESHOLD) for
          2 seconds (MAGNETIC_CALM_DURATION_MS — hysteresis prevents rapid
          toggling), switch back to TYPE_ROTATION_VECTOR. Reset tilt baseline.
      Implementation: BOTH rotation sensors are registered simultaneously
      (no re-registration gap on switch). The onSensorChanged handler gates
      which one to process via `processingRotationVector` boolean. The
      magnetic field handler runs continuously regardless of which rotation
      sensor is active. Hysteresis (15 µT trigger vs 8 µT calm + 2s duration)
      prevents oscillation at the boundary.
    - This replaces the Rev54 strategy which always preferred
      GAME_ROTATION_VECTOR. The Rev58 strategy is superior: it gets the
      accurate baseline of ROTATION_VECTOR when the environment is clean,
      and the magnetic-interference immunity of GAME_ROTATION_VECTOR when
      it's not — with automatic switching.

  v1.0.5 Round-6 Rev59 changes (CRITICAL rotation-axis fix):
    - StabilizationHelper.java (AGPL v3): CRITICAL FIX — the board's tilt-
      compensation rotation was controlled by the WRONG axis in landscape
      orientations. Root cause: SensorManager.getOrientation() was called on
      the raw device-frame rotation matrix, which returns angles in the
      DEVICE's natural coordinate system — NOT the screen's coordinate system.
      In landscape (ROTATION_90/270), the device's pitch and roll axes are
      swapped relative to what the user sees on screen. The board's rotation
      therefore responded to screen pitch (front-back nod) instead of screen
      roll (steering-wheel tilt) — exactly the bug the user reported.
      Fix: Added SensorManager.remapCoordinateSystem() call in
      processRotationVector() to transform the rotation matrix from device
      frame to screen frame BEFORE calling getOrientation(). After remapping,
      getOrientation() returns SCREEN-RELATIVE angles where values[2] is
      ALWAYS screen-roll (steering-wheel) regardless of display rotation.
      The axis-remapping parameters (xOut, yOut) are chosen per display
      rotation:
        ROTATION_0:   AXIS_X, AXIS_Y (identity)
        ROTATION_90:  AXIS_Y, AXIS_MINUS_X
        ROTATION_180: AXIS_MINUS_X, AXIS_MINUS_Y
        ROTATION_270: AXIS_MINUS_Y, AXIS_X
      Added remappedMatrix scratch array (separate from rotationMatrix to
      avoid aliasing in remapCoordinateSystem).
      SIMPLIFIED dispatchTransform() rotation: since smoothRoll is now
      ALWAYS screen-roll (the remapping handles orientation), the board
      rotation is simply -(smoothRoll - baselineRoll) for ALL 4 orientations.
      Removed the per-orientation switch for rotation — no longer needed.
      Also fixed the translation (OIS) per-orientation remapping to be
      consistent with the new understanding of device-vs-screen axes.
      VERIFICATION: Correct for ALL 4 display orientations (0°/90°/180°/270°).
      The board now ALWAYS responds to the steering-wheel angle (screen roll),
      never to the pitch (front-back nod).

  v1.0.5 Round-6 Rev64 changes (2026.6.27 remove rotation + undo cache sync):
    - StabilizationHelper.java (AGPL v3): COMPLETE REFACTOR — rotation removed
      per user spec. File slimmed from 720 → 337 lines (53% reduction).
      Deleted sensors: TYPE_ROTATION_VECTOR, TYPE_GAME_ROTATION_VECTOR,
      TYPE_MAGNETIC_FIELD (only TYPE_LINEAR_ACCELERATION retained).
      Deleted methods: processRotationVector(), processMagneticField().
      Deleted state fields: baselinePitch, baselineRoll, smoothPitch,
      smoothRoll, baselineSet, magneticBaseline, magneticBaselineSet,
      magneticCalmSince, magneticDisturbed, processingRotationVector,
      rotationMatrix[], remappedMatrix[], orientationAngles[].
      Deleted constants: MAX_ROTATION_DEG, ROTATION_DEADZONE_DEG, ROTATION_DECAY,
      TILT_ALPHA, MAGNETIC_DISTURBANCE_THRESHOLD, MAGNETIC_CALM_THRESHOLD,
      MAGNETIC_CALM_DURATION_MS, MAGNETIC_BASELINE_ALPHA.
      applyTransform(x,y) signature changed (was applyTransform(x,y,rotDeg)) —
      no longer setProperty('--stab-rot',...); added removeProperty('--stab-rot')
      to clear residual values from a previous version.
      dispatchTransform() no longer computes boardRotDeg; only translation
      (boardPxX/boardPxY) is dispatched.
      stop() calls applyTransform(0,0) (was applyTransform(0,0,0)).
      Benefits: 4 sensors → 1 sensor, lower battery, eliminates the entire class
      of rotation-direction bugs reported in Rev59-63 (rotation feature gone).
      The CSS transform (.bwrap.stabilized) was updated in index.html.tpl to
      remove the rotate(var(--stab-rot,0deg)) component — see
      chess.src/README.license Rev64 entry.

  v1.0.5 Round-6 Rev63 changes (2026.6.27 anti-shake + arrow optimization):
    - StabilizationHelper.java (AGPL v3): MAX_ROTATION_DEG reduced from ±30°
      (Rev61) to ±10° per user spec. First-principles analysis: (a) sensor
      floor ~1° (TYPE_ROTATION_VECTOR accuracy ±1°, after α=0.15 low-pass
      residual noise ~±0.5°); (b) human perception threshold ~0.5-1°; (c)
      handheld device steering-wheel tilt rarely exceeds 8° during normal
      one-handed phone use; (d) 1:1 mapping (|board rot| = |screen roll
      delta|) strictly preserved in 1°-10° range; angles beyond 10° clamped
      to prevent disorienting "board swings wildly" effect. Dead zone
      ROTATION_DEADZONE_DEG=1.0° unchanged (still correct for ±10° range).
      The CSS transform (.bwrap.stabilized) already supports arbitrary
      rotation values via the --stab-rot CSS custom property, so no CSS
      changes needed.

  v1.0.5 Round-6 Rev62 changes (2026.6.27 second-pass audit):
    - No Java file changes in this round. All fixes were in JavaScript modules
      (chess960.js, game-logic.js, tablebase.js, worker-pool.js,
      pgn-standard.js, ai-bridge.js, ui.js). See
      src/main/assets/chess.src/README.license for the JS-side Rev62 entry.

  v1.0.5 Round-6 Rev61 changes (2026.6.27 development plan):
    - StabilizationHelper.java (AGPL v3): TWO critical fixes per user spec:
      (1) Y-AXIS DIRECTION REVERSAL FIX in dispatchTransform(). All 4 screen-
          orientation cases (ROTATION_0/90/180/270) had the WRONG sign on
          boardPxY. The OIS principle requires that when the device moves UP,
          the board moves DOWN on screen (CSS +Y) to compensate. The original
          code moved the board UP on screen — amplifying the shake instead of
          cancelling it. User report: "屏幕突然向上移动，棋盘不但不向下位移
          来抵消，反而也向上". Fixed signs:
            ROTATION_0:   boardPxY = +dispY * SCALE  (was -dispY)
            ROTATION_90:  boardPxY = +dispX * SCALE  (was -dispX)
            ROTATION_180: boardPxY = -dispY * SCALE  (was +dispY)
            ROTATION_270: boardPxY = -dispX * SCALE  (was +dispX)
          X-axis signs were already correct and unchanged.
      (2) ROTATION SENSITIVITY ADJUSTMENT: ROTATION_DEADZONE_DEG enlarged from
          0.3° to 1.0° (filter sensor noise and sub-degree hand tremor);
          MAX_ROTATION_DEG reduced from 45° (Rev60) to 30° (cover normal
          handheld tilt range, avoid visual abruptness at extreme angles).
          The 1:1 ratio (|board rotation| = |screen roll delta|) is strictly
          preserved within the 1°–30° range. User report: "棋盘旋转角度过于
          敏感，屏幕小幅度转动，棋盘就大幅度转动，两者的转动角度应该绝对值
          相等才对".
    - StockfishNative.java (GPL v3, DroidFish-derived): ONE bug fix:
      (1) extractEngineFromAssets() progress percentage integer-division
          truncation fix. Original `total / 114115752L * 13` truncated
          `total / 114115752L` to 0 for any total < 114 MB (Java left-to-
          right evaluation), so progress stayed at 12% until extraction
          completed, then jumped to 25%. Fixed to `total * 13L / 114115752L`
          (multiply first, no precision loss for total < 8.8 GB).
    - StatsActivity.java (AGPL v3): ONE bug fix:
      (1) loadAssetAsBase64() stream leak fix. Original manual `is.close()`
          was only reached on the happy path — if baos.write threw (e.g.
          OutOfMemoryError on a huge asset), InputStream leaked. Switched
          to try-with-resources to guarantee closure.

  v1.0.5 Round-6 Rev60 changes (rotation limit expansion):
    - StabilizationHelper.java (AGPL v3): Increased MAX_ROTATION_DEG from
      2.0f to 45.0f per user spec. The board's tilt-compensation rotation
      can now counter-rotate up to ±45° in either direction (was ±2°). The
      low-pass filter (α=0.15) and dead zone (0.3°) ensure smooth, jitter-
      free rotation even at large angles. The CSS transform
      (.bwrap.stabilized) already supports arbitrary rotation values via
      the --stab-rot CSS custom property, so no CSS changes needed.
      NOTE: Rev61 has since reduced MAX_ROTATION_DEG from 45° back to 30°
      (see Rev61 entry above).

