  v1.0.5 Round-6 Rev67 changes (2026.6.27 landscape translation direction fix):
    - StabilizationHelper.java (AGPL v3): CRITICAL BUG FIX in dispatchTransform().
      ROTATION_90 and ROTATION_270 had boardPxX sign INVERTED — landscape
      horizontal shake was amplified instead of cancelled.
        ROTATION_90: boardPxX was -dispY*SCALE → fixed to +dispY*SCALE
        ROTATION_270: boardPxX was +dispY*SCALE → fixed to -dispY*SCALE
        ROTATION_0 (boardPxX=-dispX) and ROTATION_180 (boardPxX=+dispX) were
        already correct — unchanged.
      First-principles derivation: device-natural Dx/Dy → world-axis mapping per
      orientation, then OIS (device world-right → board screen-left CSS -x;
      device world-up → board screen-down CSS +y). Comment rewritten as a
      derivation table. Deleted old comments' incorrect orientation descriptions
      (e.g. "ROTATION_90 = device rotated CW, top points right" — actually CCW,
      top points left). Impact: landscape anti-shake horizontal direction now
      correct; portrait unaffected.

